`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The 300-line rule exists to prevent "God files" where a single module mixes types, config, entity wrappers, evaluators, and the main class all in one place — decomposing into focused subpackages makes each concern independently testable.
- When a file is the *only* non-test importer of itself, that's a clear sign it's dead production code — removing it (rather than decomposing it) reduces test maintenance burden and bundle size.
- The barrel index.ts pattern (re-exporting from subpackage files) means all import paths for callers remain `@/game/ai/NpcBrain` — no external churn when doing internal decomposition.
