`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The shim re-export pattern (`export { X } from "./subpackage/index.ts"`) at the old path lets you decompose a monolith file without touching any caller — zero import churn, zero broken tests. It's a safe migration fence.
- When a file is >300 lines, extracting a `navigation.ts` or `targeting.ts` with pure functions (that accept state as params rather than closing over `this`) makes each concern independently testable: `buildNavPath` can be called without spinning up a full `PlayerGovernor` instance.
- Removing dead code (treeGeometry.ts — 950 lines, 0 production importers) improves both build time and cognitive load more than any refactor: the best code is the code that doesn't exist.
